<p>The <code>array</code> tag retrieves multiple rows from a database table.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre>{open}array 'tablename'{close}
  {open}$fieldname{close}
{open}/array{close}</pre>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}array 'users'{close}
  &lt;li&gt;{open}$name{close} - {open}$email{close}&lt;/li&gt;
{open}/array{close}</pre>
<p>Retrieves all rows from users table and iterates over them.</p>

<h2>With Options</h2>
<pre>{open}array 'products', sort='price', rows=10{close}
  {open}$name{close}: ${open}$price{close}
{open}/array{close}</pre>
<p>Retrieves products sorted by price, limited to 10 rows.</p>

<h2>Common Options</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Option</th><th>Description</th></tr>
  <tr><td>sort</td><td>Sort by field(s)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>rows</td><td>Limit number of results</td></tr>
  <tr><td>where</td><td>Filter condition</td></tr>
  <tr><td>order</td><td>Sort direction (asc/desc)</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>Example: User List</h2>
<pre>&lt;table&gt;
  &lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Name&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Email&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Role&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
  {open}array 'users', sort='name'{close}
    &lt;tr&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;{open}$name{close}&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;{open}$email{close}&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;td&gt;{open}$role{close}&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
  {open}/array{close}
&lt;/table&gt;</pre>

<h2>Iteration Properties</h2>
<p>Standard iteration properties are available:</p>
<pre>{open}array 'items'{close}
  {open}@first ? First item{close}
  {open}@current{close} of {open}@count{close}
  {open}@last ? Last item{close}
{open}/array{close}</pre>

<h2>Comparison with PHP Data</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Source</th><th>Tag</th></tr>
  <tr><td>PHP array</td><td>{open}arrayName{close}...{open}/arrayName{close}</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Database table</td><td>{open}array 'tablename'{close}...{open}/array{close}</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Database queries require a configured database connection. This demo page does not execute live queries.</p>
